# MergeLine Support

Questions, bug reports, and feedback are welcome.

## Contact

Email: **tolgasyn2@gmail.com**

Response time is usually within 48 hours. Please include the following in bug reports so we can help you faster:

- iPhone model (for example, iPhone 15 Pro)
- iOS version (Settings → General → About → iOS Version)
- MergeLine version and build number (visible on the main menu footer)
- A short description of what you were doing when the issue happened

## Frequently Asked Questions

### The game crashed. What should I do?

Force-quit the app (swipe up and flick MergeLine off-screen), then relaunch. Your progress is saved locally after every game-over — no data is lost. If crashes keep happening, email us with the details above.

### Ads are not loading.

Ads require an internet connection. The BOMB and CONTINUE buttons use rewarded video ads — if the ad network has nothing to serve, these buttons stay disabled and you can keep playing the normal loop. This is not a bug.

### I want to opt out of personalized ads.

On first launch, iOS asks whether to allow tracking. Tap "Ask App Not to Track" for non-personalized ads. You can change this later in Settings → MergeLine → Allow Tracking.

### The Daily Challenge shows the same puzzle as yesterday.

The Daily Challenge rolls over at midnight UTC. Depending on your timezone, the change may not happen at your local midnight. For Turkey (UTC+3), the new Daily arrives at 03:00 local time.

### I lost progress after updating the app.

Progress is stored in the app sandbox and survives updates. If you deleted and reinstalled the app, local progress is cleared by iOS — this is expected behavior, not a bug.

### How do I reset my stats?

There is no in-app reset button by design. Deleting and reinstalling the app clears all local data including best tile, lifetime score, and games played.

